<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:lang="en" xml:id="terminal">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>terminal</refname>
        <refpurpose>Open an embedded terminal in the Scilab GUI</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>terminal()</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <literal>terminal</literal> opens an embedded terminal in a dockable
            Scilab tab. It is a full PTY terminal emulator (truecolor, alternate
            screen, raw input), so it can host any interactive shell command -
            in particular <emphasis>Claude Code</emphasis>
            (<literal>claude --dangerously-skip-permissions -c</literal>) - exactly
            like the terminal embedded in JetBrains IDEs.
        </para>
        <para>
            <literal>terminal</literal> has several features:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    A login shell (<literal>$SHELL -l</literal>) is started, so
                    the profile is sourced and your real <literal>PATH</literal>
                    is rebuilt (commands such as <literal>claude</literal> or
                    <literal>node</literal> resolve even when Scilab was launched
                    from the Finder/<literal>.app</literal>).
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Multiple independent sessions: each call to
                    <literal>terminal()</literal> opens a new terminal with its own
                    shell, in a dockable tab that can be floated or grouped with the
                    console, Variable Browser, SciNotes, etc.
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Configurable from
                    <emphasis>Preferences &gt; Terminal</emphasis> (shell override,
                    starting directory, scrollback, audible bell) and
                    <emphasis>Preferences &gt; Fonts</emphasis> (the
                    <literal>Terminal</literal> font).
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>
            It is also available from the
            <emphasis>Applications &gt; Terminal</emphasis> menu.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
terminal()
        ]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
